-- Qatar Deputy Premier Says Optimistic Hormuz Strait to Stay Open
-- B y   C h i s a k i   W a t a n a b e
-- 2012-03-03T10:21:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-03/qatar-deputy-premier-says-optimistic-hormuz-strait-to-stay-open.html
Qatari Deputy Prime Minister
Abdullah bin Hamad al-Attiyah is optimistic about his country’s
liquefied natural gas shipments after Iranian officials
threatened to close the Strait of Hormuz and disrupt supplies.  “I believe personally that the Strait of Hormuz will
always be open,” Attiyah said today on the sidelines of a
seminar on climate change in  Tokyo .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chisaki Watanabe in Tokyo at 
 cwatanabe5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
